# Prompt:
#   Execute the improvement plan at tools/title-loop/docs/3-a5a0dca/improvement-plan.md.
#   
#   Modify lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and any related files as needed.
#   Make sure:
#   1. All existing tests still pass
#   2. The CLI at tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts still works
#   3. The code is clean and follows the project conventions in AGENTS.md
#   4. No unnecessary changes outside the title extraction logic
#   
#   CRITICAL CONSTRAINT: Do NOT modify the substring deduplication logic in title-extractor.ts.
#   The block starting with "// Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter"
#   must remain exactly as-is. It keeps the SHORTER candidate. Do not invert this to keep the longer.
#   This has been incorrectly changed 5 times and breaks tests every time.
#   
#   After making changes, run: npx vitest run --globals lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts
#   Fix any test failures before finishing.

============================================================

All 20 tests pass. Here's a summary of everything that was done:

**Changes to `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`:**

1. **Continuation-aware `firstStructuralHeading`** (Change 2 from plan — already present, kept): filters insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter) before the structural heading check so joins like `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` qualify.

2. **`baseScore`-based threshold** (Change 3 from plan — already present, kept): uses position-free scores to compute the threshold so the first title's position boost doesn't inflate the bar and exclude valid second titles on multi-recipe pages.

3. **Continuation-extended `firstStructuralHeading`** (new): Extracted the structural heading check into `isStructuralHeading` and added a two-step selection — if the initial heading is immediately followed by a continuation token (`/`, `&`, `+`, `:`, `(`), the longer 2-line join is preferred. This is what makes SAFFRON work: `firstStructuralHeading` becomes the full join, not just the first line.

4. **Pre-dedup prefix filter** (new): Before the protected dedup block, removes candidates that are space-delimited prefixes of `firstStructuralHeading`. Guards against running when the heading itself failed the threshold. Fixed a reference equality bug (`s === firstStructuralHeading` → `s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text`) since `selected` contains new objects from `scored`, not the original `candidates` objects.

**New regression tests** (2 added): ARAYES-type (single-word prefix of 2-word heading) and SAFFRON-type (continuation-token extension of heading).

**Remaining unfixed**: `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` — mixed-case, no structural heading, so neither the continuation extension nor the prefix filter applies. Fixing it requires the dedup inversion (Change 1 from the plan) which conflicts with the explicit constraint. The partial title will be returned instead of the full title.
