{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015zD4LVaSMptEmsTehyv15K","type":"tool_result","content":"   320→\n   321→  // Use position-free baseScore for threshold so position boost on the first title doesn't\n   322→  // inflate the bar and exclude valid later titles on multi-recipe pages.\n   323→  const bestBaseScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.baseScore));\n   324→  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestBaseScore * 0.7);\n   325→\n   326→  // Filter candidates above threshold\n   327→  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n   328→\n   329→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of the firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself\n   330→  // survived the threshold. A multi-line join that qualifies as the structural heading\n   331→  // (e.g. \"ARAYES SHRAK\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\")\n   332→  // is the complete title; the first OCR line (\"ARAYES\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\")\n   333→  // is just an incomplete prefix. Without this step the dedup below would discard the\n   334→  // complete heading in favour of the shorter prefix.\n   335→  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s === firstStructuralHeading)) {\n   336→    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   337→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   338→      if (s === firstStructuralHeading) return true;\n   339→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   340→      // Keep unless s is a proper word-boundary prefix of the structural heading\n   341→      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   342→    });\n   343→  }\n   344→\n   345→  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n   346→  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n   347→  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n   348→  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n   349→    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n   350→    return !selected.some(\n   351→      (b) =>\n   352→        b !== a &&\n   353→        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n   354→        b.text.length < a.text.length\n   355→    );\n   356→  });\n   357→\n   358→  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n   359→  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0a05f64-dc5e-4fd2-9d6c-8483fb711304","uuid":"8f0d3b55-1eb0-4cdd-b2ea-94823300ebe2","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"\n  // Use position-free baseScore for threshold so position boost on the first title doesn't\n  // inflate the bar and exclude valid later titles on multi-recipe pages.\n  const bestBaseScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.baseScore));\n  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestBaseScore * 0.7);\n\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of the firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself\n  // survived the threshold. A multi-line join that qualifies as the structural heading\n  // (e.g. \"ARAYES SHRAK\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\")\n  // is the complete title; the first OCR line (\"ARAYES\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\")\n  // is just an incomplete prefix. Without this step the dedup below would discard the\n  // complete heading in favour of the shorter prefix.\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s === firstStructuralHeading)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s === firstStructuralHeading) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Keep unless s is a proper word-boundary prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).","numLines":40,"startLine":320,"totalLines":404}}}
