{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011cWGh9Dsu8fgP5pq7nM99K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 18 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Changes 2 and 3 from the plan were already implemented** (continuation-aware `firstStructuralHeading` and `baseScore`-based threshold at 0.7×).\n\n**Change 1 (dedup inversion) was intentionally skipped** per the constraint — changing \"shorter wins\" to \"longer wins\" breaks the existing unit tests.\n\n**New pre-dedup filter added** (lines 329–343): Before the protected dedup block runs, candidates that are word-boundary prefixes of `firstStructuralHeading` are removed — but only when the heading itself survived the threshold. This stops the dedup from ever seeing the prefix/heading pair:\n- **ARAYES SHRAK**: \"ARAYES\" (prefix of the structural heading) is removed → dedup keeps \"ARAYES SHRAK\" ✓\n- **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)**: \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" (prefix) is removed → full title survives ✓\n- **FINNISH MILK + POTATO FLATBREADS**: already addressed by Change 3's lower threshold ✓\n- **Baked Eggs**: no `firstStructuralHeading` (mixed case) → filter doesn't apply; the partial title will be returned instead of the full title — this case requires Change 1 to fully fix, which conflicts with the constraint\n\nProjected accuracy with these changes: **5/6 (83.3%)**, up from 33.3%."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1045,"cache_read_input_tokens":57655,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1045},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0a05f64-dc5e-4fd2-9d6c-8483fb711304","uuid":"18296d06-4b3f-464f-8c2a-509e8dff8f22"}
