{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JEiRXERSbDT9mSei33t1Ag","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Kuaxaddg7PYiKxqeFpHYmk","name":"Agent","input":{"subagent_type":"code-review-expert","description":"Review pre-dedup filter addition","prompt":"Review the following change to `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`. Focus on:\n\n1. Implementation completeness — does it fully solve the stated problem or just patch symptoms?\n2. Code quality — is the logic correct, edge cases handled, comments accurate?\n3. Integration — does the new block fit naturally with the surrounding code structure?\n4. Consistency — should the same pattern be applied elsewhere?\n\nThe change adds a pre-dedup filter between the threshold filter and the protected dedup block:\n\n```typescript\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of the firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself\n  // survived the threshold. A multi-line join that qualifies as the structural heading\n  // (e.g. \"ARAYES SHRAK\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\")\n  // is the complete title; the first OCR line (\"ARAYES\", \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\")\n  // is just an incomplete prefix. Without this step the dedup below would discard the\n  // complete heading in favour of the shorter prefix.\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s === firstStructuralHeading)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s === firstStructuralHeading) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Keep unless s is a proper word-boundary prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n```\n\nContext:\n- `firstStructuralHeading` is the first ALL_CAPS candidate with ≥2 words where every significant word (>1 alpha letter) has ≥4 alpha letters — it identifies the main recipe title heading in cookbook scans.\n- The dedup block (DO NOT CHANGE) keeps shorter candidates when one is a substring of another — correct for \"Pierogi Ruskie\" vs \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\", but wrong when \"ARAYES SHRAK\" is the complete title and \"ARAYES\" is just the first line.\n- The pre-dedup filter solves the conflict by removing the prefix BEFORE the dedup sees it.\n- All 18 existing tests pass.\n- Known limitation: \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" case (mixed-case, no structural heading) still returns the partial title — fixing it requires the dedup logic change which is explicitly prohibited.\n\nPlease read the full file at `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` and the test file at `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` before reviewing."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":537,"cache_read_input_tokens":58700,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":537},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0a05f64-dc5e-4fd2-9d6c-8483fb711304","uuid":"dccef09a-53b7-445e-ab18-31dbdc0bdd5c"}
