  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n```\n\nContext:\n- `firstStructuralHeading` is the first ALL_CAPS candidate with ≥2 words where every significant word (>1 alpha letter) has ≥4 alpha letters — it identifies the main recipe title heading in cookbook scans.\n- The dedup block (DO NOT CHANGE) keeps shorter candidates when one is a substring of another — correct for \"Pierogi Ruskie\" vs \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\", but wrong when \"ARAYES SHRAK\" is the complete title and \"ARAYES\" is just the first line.\n- The pre-dedup filter solves the conflict by removing the prefix BEFORE the dedup sees it.\n- All 18 existing tests pass.\n- Known limitation: \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" case (mixed-case, no structural heading) still returns the partial title — fixing it requires the dedup logic change which is explicitly prohibited.\n\nPlease read the full file at `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` and the test file at `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` before reviewing."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kuaxaddg7PYiKxqeFpHYmk","session_id":"a0a05f64-dc5e-4fd2-9d6c-8483fb711304","uuid":"b36a752d-4e1a-4197-a409-ca884d0beaa5"}
