ngredients\" gets removed, leaving just \"ARAYES SHRAK\" in the final selection. But the test is failing with \"ARAYES\" instead, which means something's off in my implementation—let me trace through the actual code logic...\n\nStill writing code... I'm working through the logic of how `baseHeading` gets assigned to `firstStructuralHeading` — if `baseHeading` is truthy, the expression evaluates to either the result of `candidates.find()` or falls back to `baseHeading` itself, which should preserve the full \"ARAYES SHRAK\" object. But the test is returning just \"ARAYES\", so there might be a TypeScript type issue where the union type isn't being handled correctly.\n\nReviewing the actual implementation...\n\nExamining the code logic...\n\nWhen no matching continuation is found, the nullish coalescing operator returns `baseHeading`, so `firstStructuralHeading` gets set to that value. Now I'm checking the scoring logic where it compares if a candidate object is the exact same reference as `firstStructuralHeading` to apply a structural bonus.\n\nThe reference equality check should work since `baseHeading` comes from `candidates.find()`, which returns the actual object from the array. So \"ARAYES SHRAK\" should receive the bonus and be ranked higher. But the test is still returning \"ARAYES\" instead, which suggests my pre-dedup filter isn't working as expected. Let me check what's actually in the file right now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1620,"cache_read_input_tokens":82716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1620},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0a05f64-dc5e-4fd2-9d6c-8483fb711304","uuid":"0109c0f5-a20f-4ddc-9afc-eff7d42a8a7f"}
